Former minister Nicholas Biwott toured Busia on Saturday to market his National Vision Party. He was invited to raise money for 37 women s groups at the Agricultural Training Centre. No politician from the county attended the event, which raised Sh2 million. Biwott donated Sh300,000.He said NVP will not field a presidential candidate in 2017. The party will support President Uhuru Kenyatta and Deputy President William Ruto, who will vie on the Jubilee Party ticket. We shall field candidates in all other seats, Biwott said. We want to be associated with parties that embrace peace, love and unity, he added.Biwott urged politicians to respect their rivals, not villify them. He urged residents to vote for visionary leaders who will improve their lives. The NVP chief urged Busia residents to choose development-conscious politicians.